\v 11 For the grace of God appeared,
\q2 that is bringing salvation for all people,
\q2
\v 12 teaching us
\q3 in order that
\q3 by refusing impiety and worldly desires,
\q3 we might live in a self-controlled and righteous and godly manner in this present age,
\p
\v 13 while we look forward to the blessed hope and appearing of the glory of our great God and Savior Jesus Christ,
\p
\v 14 who gave himself for us,
\p in order that he might redeem us from all lawlessness
\p and that he might cleanse for himself a people for his possession, a people zealous for good works.
